OL,3,GNorthern Ireland
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FAny light
OL,6,Fshowers dying out leaving a dry and
OL,7,Fwarm evening and staying mainly dry
OL,8,Fovernight. Thickening cloud could
OL,9,Fbring patchy rain. Winds mostly light.
OL,10,
OL,11,CThursday:FMainly dry and bright with
OL,12,Fhazy sunshine and very warm or hot.
OL,13,FOccasional thicker cloud could give
OL,14,Fthe odd burst of rain later. Light
OL,15,Fwinds with sea breezes possible.
OL,16,
OL,17,COutlook for Friday to Sunday:FShowers
OL,18,For some longer outbreaks of rain on
OL,19,FFriday and Saturday, the rain perhaps
OL,20,Fheavy and thundery at times. Bright
OL,21,Fwith scattered showers on Sunday.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
